(165, 123, 'IPH - International Private Health Super-Specialis', '1729067793.jpeg', '<div>Our goal is,</div><div>1)<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>To protect the confidentiality of our patients and respect the sensitivity of the subject every day and every way.</div><div>2)<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>To empower women with best possible private - intimate health (pelvic floor rehab) and prevent silent suffering from issues like,&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>-<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Urinary issues like – Urine leakage, difficulty to control after an urge, recurrent UTIs</div><div>-<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Bowel issues like – Constipation, difficulty to control after an urge</div><div>-<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Sexual health issues like – Loose or broad vagina, reduced vaginal tightness &amp; grip over penis, low desire, low sensations, low pleasure, orgasm difficulties, vaginal dryness, pain or discomfort during sex.</div><div>-<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Pelvic pain issues like – Pain in private parts, vagina, tail bone, ano-rectal area.</div><div>-<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Other issues like – Pelvic organ prolapse, endometriosis, interstitial cystitis</div><div>-<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Private parts health check-up – 1) Vaginal tightness check-up 2) Biomechanical check-up for breast sagging 3) Check-up for loose tummy</div><div>3)<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>To provide pelvic floor rehab super-specialty services through, latest techniques &amp; World’s 1st advanced technologies like PF 360 Focused-Tip Technology, CDSCO –FDA registered without any medicine, injection, surgery, side-effect.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '49.43.34.196', 184, NULL, '2024-10-16 08:36:33', NULL, 'ranged', NULL),
(166, 90, 'Home Health Care Services', '1731321817.jpeg', '&nbsp;Our focus is on providing high-quality, personalized care in the comfort of our patients’ homes or their most comfortable environment.&nbsp;<div>Guided by core values of empathy, care, and reliability, we ensure every service meets the highest standards.&nbsp;</div><div>We also extend our services to communities, corporates, and hospitals, offering tailored healthcare solutions such as doctor consultations, ICU Home Setup with Nursing Staff and Attendant Care, physiotherapy, nursing care, and medical equipment, Care Givers - Elder Care, Critical Care, Counselors.</div><div>Home Diagnostic Care - Blood Sample Collection, ECG, Portable X-Rays.&nbsp;</div><div>Supportive Care - Ambulance - ICU, Regular &amp; Air Ambulance, Pharmacy.&nbsp;</div><div>Our mission is to make healthcare more accessible, reliable, and personalized, while prioritizing comfort and safety.</div>', NULL, 500, 6000, NULL, 1, 0, '122.170.78.59', 150, 150, '2024-11-11 10:43:37', '2024-11-11 10:44:39', 'ranged', 'Critical care, Home Health Care, Neev Care, ICU Care, ICU Nurse, Care Givers, Palliative Care, Elderly Care, Mother and Child Care, Nanny, Old Age Care, Health Check Ups, Doctor on Call, Nurse on Call, Caretaker'),
(167, 113, 'SEMEN ANALYSIS', '1731393724.png', 'SEMEN ANALYSIS IS A VERY CRUCIAL TEST IN PATHOLOGY.<div>WE DO PROVIDE <b><u>CONVENTIONAL ROUTINE SEMEN TESTING</u></b> AND ALSO <b><u>AUTOMATED SEMEN ANALYSIS</u></b> WITH LATEST EQUIPMENTS.</div><div>WITH OUT SEPERATE SEMEN COLLECTION AREA TO LATEST INSTRUMENTS AND SKILLED PATHOLOGIST DOCTOR , WE HAVE EVERYTHING YOU NEED.</div><div>OUR DOCTOR HAS EXPERIENCE OF MORE THAN <b><u>10, 000</u></b> PLUS SEMEN ANALYSIS REPORTING.</div><div>FEEL FREE TO GET TO KNOW MORE ABOUT IT.</div><div><br></div>', NULL, 400, 1000, NULL, 1, 0, '103.240.169.79', 174, 174, '2024-11-12 06:42:04', '2024-11-12 06:52:20', 'ranged', '#SEMENANALYSIS, #SEMEN , #MALE , #FERTILITY , #REPRODUCTIVE, #LABORATORY ,#SEMEN AUTOMATED ANALYSIS, #EXPERT'),
(168, 113, 'DENGUE TEST', '1731393877.png', '<div>A <b>Dengue Test</b>&nbsp;is a diagnostic test used to detect the presence of the dengue virus or dengue antibodies in a person\'s blood.</div><div>&nbsp;Dengue fever is a mosquito-borne disease prevalent in tropical and subtropical regions, and early detection is critical for managing symptoms and preventing complications.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Here are the main types of dengue tests:</div><div><b style=\"color: var(--vz-card-color); background-color: var(--vz-card-bg); font-family: var(--vz-body-font-family); font-size: var(--vz-body-font-size); text-align: var(--vz-body-text-align);\"><br></b></div><div><b style=\"color: var(--vz-card-color); background-color: var(--vz-card-bg); font-family: var(--vz-body-font-family); font-size: var(--vz-body-font-size); text-align: var(--vz-body-text-align);\">&nbsp;1. **NS1 Antigen Test**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Detects the dengue virus itself, specifically a protein called NS1, which appears in the blood within the first few days of infection.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Effective for early diagnosis (usually within the first 5 days of symptom onset).</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Commonly used in initial screenings.</div><div><br></div><div><b>&nbsp;2. **IgM and IgG Antibody Tests**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- **IgM antibodies** are produced first, generally within 4-5 days after symptoms appear. High levels indicate a recent infection.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- **IgG antibodies** appear later (usually after 7-10 days) and remain in the blood longer, often for life, indicating past exposure or infection.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- These tests are useful for later stages of infection or for confirming a past infection.</div><div><br></div><div><b>3. **Polymerase Chain Reaction (PCR) Test**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- A highly sensitive test that detects the viral RNA, ideal for early diagnosis.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Often used for precise confirmation of dengue virus serotype.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- More costly but highly accurate.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Sample Collection and Results</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- A small blood sample is typically collected for analysis.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Results for dengue tests are generally available within a few hours to a couple of days, depending on the laboratory and test type.</div><div><br></div><div>**Important Note**: If symptoms such as high fever, severe headache, pain behind the eyes, joint pain, and rash appear, it’s essential to consult a healthcare provider for timely testing and treatment.</div>', NULL, 600, 1000, NULL, 1, 0, '103.240.169.79', 174, 174, '2024-11-12 06:44:37', '2024-11-12 06:51:14', 'ranged', '#DENGUE , #FEVER , #DENGUENS1, #NS1, #MONSOON, #MOSQUITO, #LABORATORY , #PATHOLOGY , #DOCTOR, #TEST, #CBC'),
(169, 113, 'COVID RT PCR', '1731394000.png', '<div>The **<b><u>COVID-19 RT-PCR Test</u></b>** (Reverse Transcription Polymerase Chain Reaction) is a highly accurate and reliable method used to detect the presence of SARS-CoV-2,&nbsp;</div><div>the virus that causes COVID-19. This test is considered the \"<b>gold standard</b>\" for COVID-19 diagnosis due to its sensitivity and specificity.</div><div><br></div><div>Key Aspects of the COVID-19 RT-PCR Test:</div><div><br></div><div><b>1. **Purpose**:&nbsp;</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Detects active COVID-19 infection by identifying the virus\'s genetic material (RNA) in a patient’s sample.</div><div><br></div><div><b>2. **Sample Collection**:</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- The most common sample type is a nasal or throat swab, but saliva samples can also be used in some cases.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Samples are collected by a healthcare professional, although some at-home kits are available in certain regions.</div><div><br></div><div><b>3. **Testing Process**:</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- The collected RNA from the virus is first converted to DNA through a process called reverse transcription.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- The DNA is then amplified using PCR, allowing even small quantities of the virus to be detected.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Results indicate either a positive or negative presence of the virus. A positive result confirms an active COVID-19 infection.</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>4. **Turnaround Time**:</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Results are generally available within 24-72 hours, depending on the laboratory\'s capacity and testing volume.</div><div><br></div><div><b>5. **Sensitivity and Specificity**:</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- The RT-PCR test is highly accurate and is able to detect even low levels of viral RNA.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- It remains one of the most trusted methods for diagnosing COVID-19, especially in the early stages of infection.</div><div><br></div><div><b>6. **Importance for Public Health**:</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- RT-PCR tests help in identifying infected individuals, especially asymptomatic carriers, allowing for proper isolation, treatment, and containment efforts.</div><div><br></div>', 550, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '103.240.169.79', 174, 174, '2024-11-12 06:46:40', '2024-11-12 06:49:49', 'fixed', '#COVID , #COVIDRTPCR , #HOMEVISIT , #CORONA , #RTPCR , #PCR'),
(170, 113, 'BLOOD TEST', '1731394156.png', '<div>A **<b>Blood Test</b>** is a common diagnostic tool used to assess overall health, diagnose conditions, and monitor ongoing medical conditions. Blood tests can evaluate a wide range of markers, such as blood cell counts, metabolic functions, organ health, and the presence of infections or other abnormalities.</div><div><br></div><div>### Types of Common Blood Tests:</div><div><br></div><div><b>1. **Complete Blood Count (CBC)**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Measures the levels of various blood cells, including red blood cells (RBCs), white blood cells (WBCs), hemoglobin, hematocrit, and platelets.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Useful for diagnosing infections, anemia, immune system disorders, and blood cancers.</div><div><br></div><div><b>2. **Basic Metabolic Panel (BMP)**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Evaluates blood sugar (glucose), calcium, and electrolytes (sodium, potassium, bicarbonate, and chloride) as well as kidney function (BUN and creatinine levels).</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Helps detect metabolic and kidney-related issues.</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>3. **Comprehensive Metabolic Panel (CMP)**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Includes all tests in a BMP plus additional markers for liver function (e.g., ALT, AST, ALP, bilirubin).</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Assesses overall metabolic health, including kidney and liver function.</div><div><br></div><div><b>4. **Lipid Panel**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Measures cholesterol levels, including total cholesterol, HDL (good) cholesterol, LDL (bad) cholesterol, and triglycerides.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Used to assess cardiovascular health and risk of heart disease.</div><div><br></div><div><b>5. **Thyroid Function Tests**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Includes TSH, T3, and T4 to evaluate thyroid gland function.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Helps diagnose hypothyroidism, hyperthyroidism, and other thyroid-related conditions.</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>6. **HbA1c (Hemoglobin A1c) Test**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Measures average blood sugar levels over the past 2-3 months.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Essential for managing and diagnosing diabetes.</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>7. **Liver Function Tests (LFTs)**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Evaluates liver enzymes (ALT, AST), bilirubin, and proteins to assess liver health.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Important for diagnosing liver disease, damage, or infection.</div><div><br></div><div><b>8. **Inflammation Markers (CRP, ESR)**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- **C-Reactive Protein (CRP)** and **Erythrocyte Sedimentation Rate (ESR)** measure inflammation in the body.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Helpful in detecting inflammation due to infections, autoimmune diseases, and chronic inflammatory conditions.</div><div><br></div><div><b>9. **Blood Clotting Tests (PT, aPTT)**</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Prothrombin Time (PT) and Activated Partial Thromboplastin Time (aPTT) measure blood clotting ability.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Useful in diagnosing clotting disorders and monitoring blood-thinning medications.</div><div><br></div><div>### Blood Test Procedure:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- A blood sample is drawn, typically from a vein in the arm.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- The sample is then sent to a laboratory for analysis.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Results can range from a few hours to a few days, depending on the specific tests ordered.</div><div><br></div><div>### Importance of Blood Tests:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- Blood tests are essential for preventive health, helping to detect issues early.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;- They also guide treatment plans and monitor the progression of diseases or response to treatments.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><br></div>', NULL, 150, 5000, NULL, 1, 0, '103.240.169.79', 174, NULL, '2024-11-12 06:49:16', NULL, 'ranged', '#BLOODTEST#LABORATORY#TEST#CBC#PATHOLOGY#DOCTOR'),
